      options: [
        { id: 'a', text: 'P0, P1, P2, P3, P4', isCorrect: false, explanation: 'Priority levels (P0-P4) are incident management terminology, not the severity scale used in the skill template.' },
        { id: 'b', text: 'CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW, INFO', isCorrect: true, explanation: 'Correct! The security-review skill template uses five severity levels: CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW, and INFO for each finding.' },
        { id: 'c', text: 'BLOCKER, MAJOR, MINOR, TRIVIAL', isCorrect: false, explanation: 'This is a Jira-style priority scheme, not the severity scale in the skill template.' },
        { id: 'd', text: 'ERROR, WARNING, NOTE', isCorrect: false, explanation: 'These are compiler diagnostic levels, not the security severity scale in the skill template.' },
      ],
      globalExplanation: 'The security-review skill template uses five severities: CRITICAL (immediate exploit risk), HIGH (serious vulnerability), MEDIUM (exploitable under specific conditions), LOW (minor concern), and INFO (informational finding). Each finding includes the severity, file path, line number, problem description, and concrete fix.',
